'''Alibek Sultanovich Delimkhanov''' ({{lang-ru|Алибе́к Султа́нович Делимха́нов}}) (born October 16, 1974) is a [[Chechnya|Chechen]] colonel, military commander of the [[Kadyrovtsy]] Spetsnaz battalion Sever (North).
[[Zaur Dadaev]], a former second-in-command to Alibek Delimkhanov, confessed that he had decided to kill [[Boris Nemtsov]] because of his criticism of [[Islam]] and [[Ramzan Kadyrov]], according to Russian media.<ref name=tekhnichno>{{cite news|title=Убийство Бориса Немцова раскрыли технично|url=http://kommersant.ru/doc/2683043|agency=[[Kommersant]]|date=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Для убийства Немцова нашли мотив|url=http://www.rosbalt.ru/moscow/2015/03/08/1375743.html|agency=Rosbalt|date=8 March 2015}}</ref>
