{{Infobox comic book title | title = Hothead Paisan | image = HotheadPaisan.png | caption = cover of ''Hothead Paisan'' #8 | startyr = 1991 | creators = [[Diane DiMassa]] | genre = humor }}
'''''Hothead Paisan: Homicidal Lesbian Terrorist''''' is an [[alternative comic]] written and drawn by [[Diane DiMassa]]. It features the title character wreaking violent vengeance on male oppressors. Recurring characters include Hothead's cat Chicken, her friend Roz, a talking lamp, and [[transgender]] love interest Daphne.
== Overview == The series began in 1991, published under the imprint [[Diane DiMassa|Giant Ass Publishing]], and ran to 21 issues, which were originally collected and published as two volumes: ''Hothead Paisan'' and ''The Revenge of Hothead Paisan''. These volumes were later combined and republishes as a 428-page [[Trade paperback (comics)|trade paperback]], ''The Complete Hothead Paisan'', the page-count of which includes a 10-page [[comic strip]] introduction to the main character.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Complete Hothead Paisan: Homicidal Lesbian Terrorist|last=Dimassa|first=Diane|publisher=Cleis Press|year=1999|isbn=978-1-57344-084-4|location=San Francisco|page=10|quote=|via=}}</ref>
According to Gabrielle Dean, the character of Hothead represents a "phallicized dyke" who is "at the mercy of her own rage against society, which she expresses by castrating men who are exaggerated stand-ins for the patriarchal order".<ref name="Dean">{{cite book|last1=Dean|first1=Gabrielle|editor1-last=Foster et. al|editor1-first=Thomas|title=The gay '90s : disciplinary and interdisciplinary formations in queer studies|date=1997|publisher=New York University Press|location=New York, N.Y.|isbn=978-0-8147-2673-0|page=208|chapter=The "Phallacies" of Dyke Comic Strips}}</ref>
== Musical == In 2004, a version was staged as a musical, produced by [[Bitch and Animal|Animal Prufrock]] at the [[Michigan Womyn's Music Festival]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Coble|first=Margaret|date=2004|title=Hothead Paisan (the musical) will debut at the Michigan Women's Music Festival|url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/articles/14149791/hothead-paisan-musical-will-debut-michigan-womens-music-festival|journal=Empty Closet [serial Online].|volume=|issue=371|doi=|pmid=|access-date=July 7, 2016}}</ref> The all-star cast enlisted by Animal includes [[Ani DiFranco]], [[Susan Powter|Susan "Stop The Insanity" Powter]], Ubaka Hill, [[Toshi Reagon]], Julie Wolf, Kate Wolf, and Allyson Palmer of BETTY, among others.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=qth&AN=13814354&site=ehost-live|title=Lesbian News|last=Coble|first=Margaret|date=2004|work=|issue=29|pages=38|access-date=July 7, 2016|via=LGBT Life with Full Text, Ipswich, MA.}}</ref>
