te web|url=http://blogs.edweek.org/edweek/education_and_the_media/2018/01/aes_undercover_high_series_puts_young_adults_back_in_high_school.html?cmp=SOC-SHR-FB|title=A&E's 'Undercover High' Series Puts Young Adults Back in High School|last=Walsh|first=Mark|website=Education Week - Education and the Media|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref> |- |}
=== Other television appearances === Josh has also appeared as a guest on [[Good Morning America]], [[TakePart#TakePart Live|Take Part Live]], [[Steve Harvey (TV series)|The Steve Harvey Show]], [[Anderson Live|Anderson Cooper Live]], [[The Jeff Probst Show]], and others to discuss issues related to teens, parents, and teachers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ng|first1=Christina|title=Mom Blogger Has Son Sign 18-point Agreement for iPhone|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/massachusetts-mom-son-sign-18-point-agreement-iphone/story?id=18094401|website=ABC News|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=World's Largest First Date; Harvey's Hero; Josh Shipp and Alyson Stoner: Is It Weird Teen Edition|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/steve-harvey-2013/episode-1-season-2/worlds-largest-first-date-harveys-hero-josh-shipp-and-alyson-stoner-is-it-weird-teen-edition/381205/|publisher=TV Guide|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref>
